21/08/2007
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The parties represented in parliament met with Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu on Monday (August 20th) and backed November 25th as a possible date for European Parliament elections.
The vote must be held before the end of the year.
Tariceanu says the date will be announced August 29th at the latest.
In other news Monday, the Social Democratic Party (PSD) announced that the text of a no-confidence motion it plans to file against the government would be ready within the next ten days.
The party plans to emphasise what it describes as a "major lack of equilibrium" in healthcare, education and the social benefits systems.
(Nine o'clock, Hotnews.ro - 21/08/07;
Rompres - 20/08/07)
